ian Steppe documents the Tsarist Mennonite experience through the papers of Johann Cornies (1789–1848), an ambitious and energetic leader of the Mennonite colony of Molochna.Cornies was well connected in the imperial government, and his papers offer a window not just into the world of the Molochna Mennonites but also into the Tsarist state’s relationship with the national minorities of the frontier: Mennonites, Doukhbors, Nogai Tartars, and Jews. This selection of his letters and reports, translated into English, is an invaluable resource for scholars of all aspects of life in Tsarist Ukraine and for those interested in Mennonite history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aGermanszUkraine, SouthernvCorrespondence. 0aGermanszUkraine, SouthernxHistoryy19th century. 0aMennoniteszUkraine, SouthernvCorrespondence. 0aMennoniteszUkraine, SouthernxHistoryy19th century. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / General.2bisacsh1 aDyck, Harvey L., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aEpp, Ingrid I., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aStaples, John R., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2015z978311127402708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311060681240uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144262237140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442622371423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781442622371/original  a978-3-11-060681-2  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  a978-3-11-127402-7  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL 